        <name>37.2.3.3 Choosing randomly an answer in an exam</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;An examination consists of {@n_questions@} multi-choice questions, in each of which a candidate has to deduce which one of {@n_choices@} suggested answers is correct. A completely unprepared student guesses each answer completely randomly. What is the probability that this student gets {@n_correct_ans@} or more questions correct?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]&amp;nbsp;[[feedback:prt1]]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Note:&lt;/b&gt; round your answer to 5 decimal places. Include additional zero(s) if your answer is exact with a lower number of decimal places.&lt;/p&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;SOLUTION:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Let &lt;span class="math inline"&gt;\(X\)&lt;/span&gt; be a random variable &#8216;number of answers guessed correctly&#8217; then for each question (i.e. trial) the probability of a &#8216;success&#8217; = &lt;span class="math inline"&gt;\(\dfrac{1}{{@n_choices@}}\)&lt;/span&gt;. It is clear that &lt;span class="math inline"&gt;\(X\)&lt;/span&gt; follows a binomial distribution with &lt;span class="math inline"&gt;\(n={@n_questions@}\)&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;span class="math inline"&gt;\(p={@1/n_choices@}\)&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="math inline"&gt;\(\text{P}\)&lt;/span&gt; (randomly choosing correct answer) &lt;span class="math inline"&gt;\(=\dfrac{1}{{@n_choices@}}\qquad n={@n_questions@}\)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="math display"&gt;\[\begin{aligned}
\text{P} ({@n_correct_ans@}\ \text{or more correct})&amp;amp;=\text{P} [(X={@n_correct_ans@})\cup (X={@n_correct_ans+1@})\cup (X={@n_correct_ans+2@})]\\
&amp;amp;=\  ^{{@n_questions@}}\!C_{@n_correct_ans@}\left(\dfrac{1}{{@n_choices@}}\right)^{@n_correct_ans@}\left(\dfrac{@n_choices-1@}{@n_choices@}\right)^2+\  ^{{@n_questions@}}\!C_{@n_correct_ans+1@}\left(\dfrac{1}{{@n_choices@}}\right)^{@n_correct_ans+1@}\left(\dfrac{{@n_choices-1@}}{{@n_choices@}}\right)+\  ^{{@n_questions@}}\!C_{{@n_questions@}}\left(\dfrac{1}{{@n_choices@}}\right)^{{@n_questions@}} \\ &amp;amp; ={@dispdp(ta,5)@}\end{aligned}\]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</generalfeedback>
